Package com.library.database.entities

Interface DBEntity

All Known Implementing Classes:
Author, Book, BookForm, BookInventory, EventNotification, Reader, ReaderRating, User
public interface DBEntity
The DBEntity interface is a marker interface that represents an entity in the database. Classes implementing this interface are expected to model entities stored in the database.

This interface serves as a common base interface for all database entities and is typically used to indicate that a class is an entity, allowing for generic processing of entities in certain situations.

Implementing classes should provide appropriate implementations for equals, hashCode, and any other relevant methods based on the business logic of the entity.
